LLMs, who do understand the deep parts of the math behind it. So once there's a cross-pollination,

00:19:39.520 --> 00:19:43.680
like together they're learning, you know, some of them come from research, they're not very used to

00:19:43.680 --> 00:19:48.560
how to work in a product environment, how to build product features, but they know how, they understand

00:19:48.560 --> 00:19:52.719
the math and the research and then vice versa, right? These folks don't understand the depth of

00:19:52.719 --> 00:19:58.239
LLMs, but they do understand how to produce good models and output things. So it's a cross-pollination.

00:19:58.239 --> 00:20:03.599
I've also had to like set up what I'm calling the center of excellence, because with ChadGPT,

00:20:03.599 --> 00:20:07.680
I think you technically don't even need a data scientist to run these prompts. Like everybody

00:20:07.680 --> 00:20:13.520
in my company is running stuff using prompts and building assistance as they call it for

00:20:13.520 --> 00:20:18.239
different purposes. So I've really had to set up the center of excellence around like teaching

00:20:18.239 --> 00:20:23.760
and teaching how these things work, even being technical, talking about evaluations, talking

00:20:23.760 --> 00:20:29.920
about hallucinations, what they could mean. And so it's become a constant like teaching,

00:20:29.920 --> 00:20:33.439
providing guardrails, you know, making sure people are thinking about the right things.

00:20:33.920 --> 00:20:39.199
Because math can be learned by people who want to, and who are also probably, it's easier,

00:20:39.199 --> 00:20:43.599
but there's also a whole plethora of people using these tools that are not going to learn the math.

00:20:43.599 --> 00:20:49.920
So it's really making it consumable for them in a way that, you know, taking the probabilistic idea,

00:20:49.920 --> 00:20:53.439
but again, teaching them in a simpler way that they would still have that intuition rather than

00:20:53.439 --> 00:21:00.239
knowing the math. So that's been a big part of what I focused on for the half of last year.

00:21:00.239 --> 00:21:06.079
And I think I'll continue having to do that, do more. And we're doing that more specifically with

00:21:06.079 --> 00:21:12.079
cohorts of different groups from business and sales and all of that as well now. So thank you.

00:21:13.520 --> 00:21:20.000
Amazing. Your answers are so thorough. I love them so much. You're like covering all the follow-ups

